      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HARA'S FRANKIE (8) was in the minors two back (25.41) at this track but ran below best last time at Q Parklands, finishing 8th. Form here at the trip sound including three wins. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings four times from eight starts. Tough to beat if on-song. ASTON BARBIE (4) was a strong winner (21.83) from box 3 last time, scoring by 2.25 lengths at this track. Will need some luck early after drawing a tricky box here. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to her name from four starts. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. SUMMER'S EDITION (1) shapes nicely here coming off a dominant 23.47 win at Rockhampton over 407m. In form and must include in calculations. NANGAR ZARA (6) profiles nicely over this trip.",
